{
  "texts": [
    "There exists a positive integer m 0 such that the family {k} ∪ {Q(ζ ℓ)} ℓ≥m0:prime is linearly disjoint over Q.",
    "We know that Q(ζ ℓ) for all prime numbers ℓ are linearly disjoint over Q.",
    "Hence the lemma follows from [FriJ23, Lemma 3.1.10].",
    "□ Let φ denote the Euler totient function, i.e., φ(n) for a positive integer n is the number of positive integers less than or equal to n that are coprime to n.",
    "Let K be a finitely generated field over Q and a an element in K × which is not a root of unity."
  ]
}